    "faqItems": [
      {
        "q": "Is digital time tracking mandatory?",
        "a": "Yes. Since 2019, Royal Decree-Law 8/2019 requires all companies to record their employees' working hours. Torre Tempo complies with all legal requirements."
      },
      {
        "q": "Does it work offline?",
        "a": "Yes. The app works offline and syncs clock-ins when the connection is restored. No clock-in is ever lost."
      },
      {
        "q": "Can I export the data for my payroll provider?",
        "a": "Yes. Export in CSV format compatible with Sage, A3, Meta4 and other payroll systems."
      },
      {
        "q": "How does geofencing work?",
        "a": "You set a radius around each location. Employees can only clock in when they're within the area."
      },
      {
        "q": "What happens if a labor inspector requests the records?",
        "a": "Torre Tempo generates read-only access tokens for ITSS inspectors. Every record has SHA-256 verification."
      },
      {
        "q": "How long does implementation take?",
        "a": "You can be up and running in under 10 minutes. Create the organization, add employees and start clocking in."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is there a minimum commitment?",
        "a": "No. Monthly billing with no commitment. You can cancel anytime."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is it GDPR compliant?",
        "a": "Yes. Personal data is encrypted with AES-256-GCM. We comply with Organic Law 3/2018 on Data Protection."
      }
    ],
